teSize` and `isScalaClass`, are set to true, and only work with objects in the scala package. It's crucial to avoid placing tests in the same package as the library and to have a public API. I might consider using `scala.collection.immutable.List`, but if `Class.forName` fails due to a missing class, that complicates things. Adding scala-xml could help resolve this. I should also cover the need for compatible dependency versions and address the inclusion of class metadata for Native Image builds, which might require reflection configuration for proper accessibility.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Native Image class resolution**\\n\\nFor the Native Image, I'm thinking that `Class.forName` with a string constant should work if the class is reachable. That seems likely, but I wonder about the runtime situation. If the class isn’t included during the build process, it could cause issues when trying to find it later. It's crucial that everything needed is accounted for at the build time to avoid runtime errors. I'll need to keep this in mind while setting up the Native Image.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8PVnoeVeQBCKXT6s7kgzcbhL|fc_0e09daeb52a7b8030169f52d81b97081a3a7a855ce0592dc92", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"scala-xml|xml.Node|scala.xml\" -n tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8 local_repositories/source_context/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/main/extracted | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 12008, "output": 1105, "cacheRead": 6144, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19257, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777675628512, "responseId": "resp_0e09daeb52a7b8030169f52d6d52f881a39cf4b69870499165"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8PVnoeVeQBCKXT6s7kgzcbhL|fc_0e09daeb52a7b8030169f52d81b97081a3a7a855ce0592dc92", "toolName": "bash", "con